1686	  \(\mathbb{Z}[X^I, 1/P^I_J]\) and \(\delta_{I,J}\) is surjective. Concretely the
1687	  closed subscheme \(\Delta_{I,J} \subseteq U^I \times_{\mathbb{Z}} U^J\) is cut
1688	  out by the entries of the matrix relation
1689	  \[
1690	    X^J_I \, X^I - X^J \;=\; 0,
1691	  \]
